President Joe Biden has announced his intent to nominate two individuals for key positions in U.S. foreign policy and aid. The first nominee is Thomas Barrett, who is being considered for the role of Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary to the Grand Duchy of Luxembourg. Barrett has been the Mayor of Milwaukee since 2004 and is currently the nation's longest-serving big city mayor. He has also served as a Member of the U.S. House of Representatives and has a background in clean and green initiatives. The second nominee is Carla Koppell, who is being considered for the position of Assistant Administrator for Development, Democracy, and Innovation at the United States Agency for International Development (USAID). Koppell is an international affairs expert with a focus on development assistance and conflict resolution. She has held various roles in government and organizations such as USAID and the U.S. Institute of Peace, where she worked on issues related to gender equality, climate change, and peacebuilding in conflict zones.